{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase highway funding & ringfence fuel duty & road tax for road maintenance",
        "additional_details": "We believe the current funding model is failing. Motorist taxes make around \u00a330 billion annually; the 2024 Autumn Budget allocated only around \u00a31.6 billion for local highways. We feel this disparity has left parts of our road network in poor condition.\r\n \r\nNottinghamshire County Council has inherited a backlog of around \u00a3391 million. To stop roads deteriorating further, we need higher government grants to ensure repairs do not fall short.",
        "background": "We want the Government to increase capital highway funding for local authorities and ringfence a fixed percentage of revenue from the Fuel Duty Tax and Road Tax to meet the \u201csteady state\u201d maintenance requirement and allow for a permanent structural repair.",
